<text x="1127.76" y="294.64" size="3.81" layer="96">Composite Video</text>
<wire x1="1125.22" y1="299.72" x2="1125.22" y2="373.38" width="0.1524" layer="95"/>
<text x="1033.78" y="241.3" size="3.81" layer="96">Resistor Ladder DAC</text>
<text x="266.7" y="368.3" size="3.81" layer="96">RTC Battery</text>
<text x="1033.78" y="172.72" size="3.81" layer="96">Raspberry Pi Pico</text>
<wire x1="1125.22" y1="246.38" x2="1181.1" y2="246.38" width="0.1524" layer="95"/>
<text x="266.7" y="302.26" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
Coin Cell Should Be able to power the ATTINY85</text>
<text x="1127.76" y="248.92" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
Composite video connector is entirely optional,
but has been retained in case it's desired. 
Ensure a jumper is fitted to CN4.</text>
<text x="1031.24" y="248.92" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
On board slide Power Switch, with the option for an off board toggle switch as well. </text>
<text x="1033.78" y="182.88" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
VGA DAC, as based off the design as found in the "Hardware design with RP2040". 
DAC's retained to allow for compatability with the optional composite output. 

This board is designed to be compatible with the 128/512/Plus.  However, it should also work with the SE and SE/30. 
Would not surprise me if it works with a Classic and Classic ii as well.</text>
<text x="1127.76" y="302.26" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
Pull downs on the Mac Video Lines to form 
potential dividers, just in case they're needed,
otherwise DNF.</text>
<text x="1033.78" y="60.96" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
Pico Header and Pinout, again taken from the reference material.
22R inline resistors for some protection. 
Found that the video output from a plus board is only about 3-4v, within tolerance of a standard Pico. 
R22, R23, R24 are present but DNF'd, in case they are needed (I.E, with an SE board)</text>
<text x="1127.76" y="368.3" size="3.81" layer="96">Video Input Pulldowns</text>
<text x="1049.02" y="2.54" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
It's a VGA port. What else do you want from me?</text>
<text x="1031.24" y="302.26" size="1.778" layer="95">Engineers Note:
Board should work with a Pico ATX PSU, to make it a "double Pico" design. 
Any other ATX power supply should be fine though.</text>
<wire x1="1181.1" y1="180.34" x2="1181.1" y2="55.88" width="0.1524" layer="95"/>
